`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The save system uses **two parallel persistence layers**: Legend State `syncObservable` + expo-sqlite kv-store for reactive observables (player state, chunk diffs), and drizzle-orm relational tables for structured data (trees, resources, unlocks). Both are valid — the kv-store is simpler for arbitrary JSON shapes, relational tables enable structured queries.
- `chunkDiffs$` was already fully implemented with in-memory delta-only storage (only modified chunks stored, zero cost for exploration). The missing piece was wiring it to SQLite so diffs survive app restarts — a single `syncObservable` call with a unique `name` key completes it.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

